snippet.textDisplay: I could really bash on Don in a five paragraph revised and edited essay, but I know you don’t want to read that. And just a side-note, I’m half Filipino and half Samoan so I understand the pressures that come with being raised in a communal setting. It’s tough it really is-because we often define our happiness and success through the happiness and prosperity of the ones we love. We try so hard to give our ALL to every one around us, spreading the wealth, energy, love, support, value, etc, that it becomes almost inevitable for us to spread ourselves too thin. From there is a breaking point(they fixed humpty dumpty though🤷🏽‍♂️) where if we don’t practice (like what you said), “Self-Care and Self-Love”, we can easily lose ourselves. Another great point that you added- is to surround yourself with people that uplift you and remind yourself of who YOU are. I believe that’s crucial first and foremost, before you can start writing down goals and manifesting all of your dreams/aspirations. Currently I’m stuck in Hawaii, but actually live in Washington... yeah I’m not proud of it...especially with everything happening there. I come here to help out with my grandparents and spend time/talk story with my auntys and uncles. Whenever I come back to the islands, I receive clarity as to both: what my purposes are and what steps I need to take in order to get myself there. But I think it’s deeper than that, I receive clarity with my family because they remind me of who I am (Strengths, Weaknesses,Values,Virtues) and who I want to become. AND I can TRUST that they are always looking out for my best interest. At the end of the day, our first investment has to be in ourselves. Yo I really didn’t mean to comment this much, but I just kept typing through the Grace of God. I just want to radiate positive vibes to you because you are such an inspiration to the Filipino population. More so now than ever you should feel ultimate beauty and strength within yourself- because you are so damn strong. Believe that Liane. ❤️🙏🏽

snippet.textDisplay: I definitely know exactly how you feel. My ex husband and I were married/together for 4 years and have a child together yet he still cheated and left... and now he’s with the person he cheated for. Shocking thing is he cheated on me not with a real woman.. I’ve been going through this pain for half a year now. He comes back to try to take custody of my son and telling me he will not pay me any support while I’ve been the primary parent. I also am a forgiving person, I gave my ex husband so many chances after what he did. He used me and manipulated me for his own gains. You really cannot do this alone. It is really hard and times you think you just can’t do it anymore but remember God is challenging you and making you stronger. Everyday I would feel sad and cry but you just have to stay strong and think about your bright future and goals. God does have other paths for you. Stay strong 💪 Liane!
